narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Musi 460-463 is one of the main reasons I came to Yale, and it hasn't disappointed. It's fantastic to be able to spend a great deal of my time practicing and earn a grade and course credit for all that work I put in. Most liberal arts schools aren't willing to give grades for a non-academic subject, but I'm so glad that Yale is - it makes Yale one of the only schools in the country where liberal arts students can fully incorporate a part-time conservatory-level study of music into their curricula. Ultimately, it fosters a high level of artistry in the undergraduate community that would be simply infeasible otherwise.
I would recommend the private instruction to every student who is interested in improving their instrumental musicianship.
